{'hadithnumber': 551, 'text': 'On Friday, when the Imam is delivering the Khutbah (religious talk), if you say to your companion to keep quiet, then indeed you have committed a sin (error/something senseless).'}
{'hadithnumber': 552, 'text': 'A man entered the mosque on a Friday when the Prophet (ﷺ) was delivering the Khutbah (religious talk, sermon) and he  said, "Stand and pray two Rak\'at."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 553, 'text': "The Prophet (ﷺ) used to recite in Jumu'ah prayer Surat al-Jumu'ah and al-Munafiqun.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 554, 'text': 'He  used to recite in the two \'Eids and in the Friday prayer: "Sabbih isma Rabbikal-A\'la (Surat 87)" and "Hal ataka hadithul-ghashiyah (Surat 88)."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 555, 'text': 'The Prophet (ﷺ) prayed the \'Eid prayer (on a Friday); and granted a permission (to be excused) from the praying of Friday prayer and said, "Whoever wants to pray it, he may pray."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 556, 'text': 'Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) said: "When anyone of you prays the Jumu\'ah prayer, he should pray four (optional) Rak\'at after it."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 557, 'text': 'That we should not connect a prayer to another prayer till we talk or go out (in between them)."\\n\\n'}
{'hadithnumber': 558, 'text': 'Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) said: "Whoever takes a bath, then comes to al-Jumu\'ah prayer, then prays what was fixed for him, then keeps silent till the Imam finishes the Khutbah (religious talk - sermon), and then prays along with him - his sins (committed) between that time and the next Friday will be forgiven, with an addition of three days more."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 559, 'text': 'Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) mentioned the day of al-Jumu\'ah and then said, "There is a time in it (Friday) at which no Muslim would stand up while praying and beg Allah, Who is Great and Glorious, for something except that He would give it to him. He (ﷺ) indicated with his hand that it (this time) is short."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 560, 'text': '"This time is brief."'}
{'hadithnumber': 561, 'text': 'I heard Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) say, "That time is between the time when the Imam sits down and the end of the prayer."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 562, 'text': "Ibn Majah reported from 'Abdullah bin Salam"}
{'hadithnumber': 563, 'text': '"It is between the \'Asr prayer and sunset."'}
{'hadithnumber': 564, 'text': "More than forty different sayings were narrated about this (special fortune time on Friday), and I have detailed them in (my book) 'Sharh al-Bukhari'."}
{'hadithnumber': 565, 'text': 'It is decided in the Sunnah that the Friday prayer  (established/recognized) when forty praying persons or more attend it.\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 566, 'text': "The Prophet (ﷺ) used to ask for (Allah's) forgiveness for the believing men and believing women, every al-Jumu'ah (Friday prayer).\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 567, 'text': "The Prophet (ﷺ) used to recite some verses from the Qur'an in the Friday Khutbah (religious talk - sermon), reminding the people.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 568, 'text': 'And its basic meaning is in Muslim.'}
{'hadithnumber': 569, 'text': 'Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) said: "The Friday prayer in congregation is an obligatory duty upon every Muslim, with the exception of four: a slave, a woman, a child and a sick person."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 570, 'text': 'al-Hakim also reported it from the narration of the aforementioned Tariq, who narrated from Abu Musa.'}
{'hadithnumber': 571, 'text': 'Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) said: "Jumu\'ah prayer is not obligatory on a traveller."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 572, 'text': "Whenever Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) ascended the Minbar (to give the Friday Khutbah), we used to face him.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 573, 'text': "It has a Shahid (supporting narration) in the Hadith of al-Bara', reported by Ibn Khuzaimah."}
{'hadithnumber': 574, 'text': 'We attended the Friday prayer with the Prophet (ﷺ) and he (ﷺ) stood leaning on a staff or a bow.\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 575, 'text': "Narrated Salih bin Khawwat on the authority of one who offered the Fear prayer with Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) at the battle of Dhatur-Riqa' that a group (of the army) formed a line along with him and a group faced the enemy. He (ﷺ) led the group which was with him in a Rak'ah, and then remained standing while they finished their prayer by themselves. They then departed and lined up facing the\\nenemy, and the other party came. He led them in the remaining Rak'a (of his\\nprayer), after which he remained sitting while they finished their prayer by\\nthemselves. He then led them in uttering the Taslim (salutation).\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 576, 'text': 'from Salih ibn Khawwat, from his\\nfather.'}
{'hadithnumber': 577, 'text': "I went on an expedition with Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) to Najd, and when we came in front of the enemy we lined up in ranks facing them. Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) then stood up and led us in prayer. One group stood up with him while the other faced the enemy. He prayed a Rak'ah with those who were with him and made two prostrations. Then, they changed places with those who had not prayed. When they came Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) prayed a Rak'ah with them and made two prostrations. He then uttered the Taslim (salutation) and each of them got up and prayed a Rak'ah alone and made two prostrations.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 578, 'text': '"I witnessed Salat-al-Khauf with Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) and we lined up in two rows behind him with the enemy between us and the Qiblah. The Prophet (ﷺ) uttered the Takbir and we all uttered it; then he bowed and we all bowed; then he raised his head after bowing and we all raised ours; then he and the row immediately behind him went down in prostration while the rear row stood facing the enemy. Then, when Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) finished the prostration and the row immediately behind him stood up..." then he mentioned the Hadith.\\n\\nAnd in a narration "Then he prostrated and the first row prostrated with him.  So when they stood, the second row prostrated then the first row went back and the second row came forward..." then he mentioned a similar to it.\\n\\nAnd at the end of it "Then the\\nProphet (ﷺ) uttered the Taslim (salutation) and we all did so."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 579, 'text': '"it was in Usfan."'}
{'hadithnumber': 580, 'text': 'The Prophet (ﷺ) led a group of his Companions in two Rak\'at after which he uttered the Taslim (salutation). Then he led another group in two Rak\'at after which he uttered the Taslim (salutation)."'}
{'hadithnumber': 581, 'text': 'Abu Dawud has reported similarly from Abu Bakrah (RA).'}
{'hadithnumber': 582, 'text': "The Prophet (ﷺ) performed Salatal-Khauf leading these (Companions) in one Rak'ah and those (other Companions) in one Rak'ah, and they did not make up the second Rak'ah.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 583, 'text': "Ibn Khuzaimah has reported it similarly from Ibn 'Abbas (RA)."}
{'hadithnumber': 584, 'text': 'Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) said: "The prayer in time of danger is one Rak\'ah, in whatever manner it is (performed)."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 585, 'text': '(This Hadith is) attributed to the Prophet (ﷺ) "There is no Sahw (prostration for forgetfulness) in the prayer in time of danger."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 586, 'text': 'Allah\'s Messenger (ﷺ) said: "(\'Eid) al-Fitr is the day on which the people break the fast, and (\'Eid) al-Adha is the day the people offer sacrifices."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 587, 'text': "Narrated Abu 'Umair bin Anas bin Malik (RA) on the authority of some of his paternal uncles who were among the Companions, that some riders came and testified that they had seen the new moon the previous day. The Prophet (ﷺ) therefore commanded the people to break the fast and go out to their place of prayer in the morning.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 588, 'text': "Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) would not go out on the day of the breaking of the fast till he ate some dates, which he used to eat in odd numbers.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 589, 'text': '"and he used to them one by one."'}
{'hadithnumber': 590, 'text': "Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) would not go out on the day of breaking of the fast till he had some food, and he would not to take any food on the day of sacrifice till he had prayed (the 'Eid prayer).\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 591, 'text': "We were commanded to bring out on 'Eidul-Fitr and 'Eidul-Adha, the young women and the menstruating women to participate in the goodness and supplications of the Muslims. However, the menstruating women would refrain from the (actual) place of prayer.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 592, 'text': "Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) Abu Bakr and 'Umar (RA) used to offer the 'Eid prayer before the Khutbah (religious talk - sermon).\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 593, 'text': "The Prophet (ﷺ) offered two Rak'at on the day of 'Eid, and did not pray before or after them.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 594, 'text': "The Prophet (ﷺ) offered the 'Eid prayer without an Adhan or an Iqamah.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 595, 'text': 'And its basic meaning is in al-Bukhari.'}
{'hadithnumber': 596, 'text': "The Prophet (ﷺ) never used to offer any prayer before the 'Eid prayer. But when he went back home, he used to pray two Rak'at.\\n\\n."}
{'hadithnumber': 597, 'text': 'The Prophet (ﷺ) used to go out on the day of the breaking of the fast and the day of sacrifice to the place of prayer, and the first thing he would start with was the prayer. When he finished he would stand facing the people, who were seated in their rows, and he would then preach to them and command them.\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 598, 'text': 'The Prophet of Allah (ﷺ) said: "The Takbir in (\'Eid) al-Fitr prayer are seven in the first Rak\'ah and five in the second, and the recitation of the Qur\'an in both is after the Takbir."\\n\\n.'}
{'hadithnumber': 599, 'text': 'at-Tirmidhi transmitted its Tashih (grading of\\nauthenticity) from al-Bukhari.'}
{'hadithnumber': 600, 'text': "The Prophet (ﷺ) used to recite on ('Eid) al-Adha and ('Eid) al-Fitr, Surat Qaf (Chapter 50) and Surat Al-Qamar (Chapter 54).\\n\\n."}
